    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> basmati rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>garam masala, ground coriander</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>sultanas </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Add<strong> </strong>350ml<strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and stir it all together, then cover tightly with<strong> tin foil</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 30-35 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>coconut rice</strong></p>",
